channel.title: Help! Made new Client But
channel.description: ok everyone i made my first client after hosting my server on others [mopar, silab]. So i have the client up and everything is well. But, i have null items. i know that nulls mean that the item isnt added to my client yet. so how can i fix this problem.? a link to a tut or something else would be very great. ty for reading. :) also you will be added to the credits list for helping with the nulls. :D

item.title: Help! Made new Client But
item.dc:creator: @I_Buck_I I Buck I
item.description:
@I_Buck_I wrote:

Null’s usually mean that the clients id’s are different from the server ones. look in item.java and item2.java and item.cfg (not sure correct me if I’m wrong) and change the ones to match the client so it will be compatible.

Read full topic

item.description:

kind of a hard thing to fix if you’re entirely new. you have to find the gzipped model and add it to your models folder, as well as add all the new ints and stuff in class8.java

here’s a useful site for that kind of stuff.
http://runescape-models.freehostia.com/
